t` component, enhanced with a vanilla JS accordion. Surveys will use IBlocks for questions/answers and Highload Blocks to store results, accessed via AJAX. I\u0027m also reiterating the testing workflow on the test server, emphasizing template isolation and folder structure. Setting up the core CSS variables and the base template looks like a good starting point.\n\n\n**Defining the Design Elements**\n\nI\u0027m now nailing down the aesthetic and technical design specifics. I\u0027ll utilize a `variables.css` file to establish CSS variables for reusability. I\u0027m focusing on \"frosted glass\" effects for cards and panels via `backdrop-filter: blur`. For the page implementations, I\u0027m thinking of how I will use the `news.list` component and handle the documents section using IBlocks. I\u0027m keeping vanilla JS and CSS as a priority for all pages.\n\n\n**Implementing the Surveys**\n\nThe survey module will use vanilla JS for a modal UI, dynamically rendering questions from an IBlock. A custom PHP handler (`ajax.php`) will process the results, calculate a score, and store them in a Highload Block or IBlock. I\u0027m excited to get that built! The goal is to start with the foundational `header.php`, `footer.php`, and `style.css` using CSS variables to build up the base framework.\n\n\n",
